eNCA's Heidi Giokos reports. Courtesy #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - Government's assurances and action are normally the two most important things that keep countries going during pandemics. For South Africa though, mixed messages have caused confusion and anger. READ: COVID-19 in SA: Stricter restrictions recommended On 6 May, eNCA reporter Masego Rahlaga asked Health Minister Zweli Mkhize why government is not heeding calls to close the borders and just on Saturday, acting Health Minister Mmamoloko Kubayi-Ngubane, announced that the Delta variant is driving Gauteng's third wave of infections. eNCA's Heidi Giokos takes a closer look in the video above.